JOBURG MetroBus staff including bus drivers and
mechanics have downed tools. Most of the bus services were affected by
the strike. While Gandhi Square became a ghost town on
Monday morning, as bus services were suspended, and commuters had to take
alternative transport.  The only available means of transport was taxis;
however, many were left stranded when they arrived at taxi ranks. The influx of commuters meant that taxis
were not enough to transport all the commuters at the time. The Democratic Municipal and Allied
Workers' Union of South Africa (Demawusa) their members are embarking on a
strike in support of demands that they be paid according to their experience.      